The paper deals with the capacity of memoryless channels with deletion errors, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses upper bounds on the capacity, which involves the use of concatenation and weighted averages, which are techniques commonly used in coding theory and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the deletion/substitution channel, which is a type of error-correcting code, and thus falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the stability of the deletion channel, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques such as optimization and probability theory, which are also used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
